    {
      "id": "C1jYc2PTyZIjQd2Iyt7V",
      "title": "Lease out",
      "description": "A type of 'Sell' activity where the actor, as the owner or provider (the lessor), sells the right for another party (the lessee) to use an asset for a specified period. Unlike other 'Sell' activities, this does not transfer permanent ownership of the asset itself. This category covers granting temporary use of property, equipment, or other assets in exchange for regular payments. It includes both formal, long-term arrangements, often called 'leasing', and more informal, short-term arrangements, often called 'renting'. Synonyms: Lease",
      "synsets": "",
      "actionAlternatives": []
    },
