    {
      "id": "ivPKQuvb3SRqjtIKqn4d",
      "title": "Sell",
      "description": "An activity of transferring ownership of, or the right to use, a good, service, or asset to another party in exchange for money or an equivalent form of payment. The defining characteristic of selling is the transaction for payment. This distinguishes it from other forms of provision or transfer, such as 'Give' (a gift) or 'Trade' (barter). The scope of this activity is broad, encompassing the entire process of making something available for purchase, including not only the final exchange but also preparatory activities like marketing and advertising. What is sold can be the permanent ownership of an item (e.g., a physical object or information) or the temporary right to use an asset (e.g., leasing or renting). Synonyms: Market, Sell",
      "synsets": "Market.v.01, Sell.v.01",
      "actionAlternatives": []
    },
